				<h2>Wences Casares, Founder and CEO, Xapo</h2>
				<div class="bio">Wences is a global, financial technology entrepreneur. He is currently founder &amp; CEO of Bitcoin pioneer Xapo, and serves on the board of Endeavor, a non-profit that supports high-impact entrepreneurs globally. Previously, he founded successful technology and financial ventures in the US, South America and Europe. He founded Argentina’s first Internet Service Provider (ISP) before dropping out of college, and then went on to found Patagon, Latin America’s premier online brokerage, which was acquired by Banco Santander. He later founded Banco Lemon, a Brazilian retail bank, as well as mobile payment companies Bling Nation and Lemon Wallet.
				</div>
			</div>
		</div>
